main event: Ten to fifteen objects were observed flying in a straight line from west to east at an estimated altitude of 30,000 to 60,000 feet in San Jose, California.
interesting points: The objects were observed during daylight and appeared to be shaped like painted objects., The observation lasted from 0945 to 1015 PDST., The report indicates insufficient data and no follow-up was requested., No additional witnesses were reported for this unusual sighting., The objects vanished to the east after the observation.
witness description: Frank Clark, the individual who reported the sighting.
